RXZlbnQyODExNzg4NTk0"},"status":1},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1574176473,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU1NTU1MjkwMg==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/76#issuecomment-555552902"},"message":"\u003e xxh3's benchmark suite has problem. it make use of \"deep hided\" function pointers, preventing function inlining. Thus wyhash is biased to low speed/throughput. By direct calling wyhash, it is faster than xxh3 and close to FNV1A_Pippip_Yurii\n\nThat's true, still working on that. (templated hashfunc classes, branch hashapi) \nBut on the other hand wyhash switch{} benefits from compile-time known len values #85.\nBoth issues need to be fixed.\ntestall.sh completed now after 4 days, will update your v3 now.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"a8f5cc6e3ca5c3c08a52bd4ccf655efd7b4bcadf"},"timestamp":1574176539,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU1NTU1MzM5Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/76#issuecomment-555553393"},"message":"wyhash newer version has no switch, just using xxh3's finalization method ;-)","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1574176771,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDU1NTU1NDk3Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/76#issuecomment-555554973"},"message":"Ah, hope it's still good enough then. I just to move xxh3 from GOOD to POOR, due to too many collisions in its lower 32bits.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1574176771,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdDMxMTU3OTg0Mw=="},"target":"cccb03062ee0456a8fa77f8e7929fb5c32038624b383f668bb575d3478870634","message":"Ah, hope it's still good enough then. I just had to move xxh3 from GOOD to POOR, due to too many collisions in its lower 32bits.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"a8f5cc6e3ca5c3c08a52bd4ccf655ef